<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 19 at 12:18PM EST  by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly</headline>
<description>...Snow Squall Approaching The Area ...
A fast moving and intense snow squall along an arctic cold front is
currently approaching the area as it moves eastward from central PA
and upstate NY. This squall may start to weaken as it moves into
portions of eastern PA and northern NJ but may still be capable of
producing a brief rapid drop in visibility to a quarter mile or less
in heavy snow along with winds gusting to 50 mph.
Expect the line of snow showers and potential squalls to arrive in
Berks County northward through the Lehigh Valley and the southern
Poconos within the 1 to 2 PM timeframe and reach northwestern New
Jersey within the 2 to 3 PM timeframe. The most intense portion of
any squalls should last no more than 10 to 15 minutes at any one
location.</description>
